daily_routine: Dawn prayers at the river shrine her grandmother built. Checking traditional
  bamboo fish traps that catch nothing now. Listening for the old river sounds - bird
  calls, water currents - drowned out by cargo ship engines. Teaching Mandarin-speaking
  grandchildren Anhui dialect words they'll never use.
